The paper deals with set quantifier alternation hierarchies in modal logic, which are closely related to topics in logic and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves the study of finite graphs, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the use of modal logic in the paper could make it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
